Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Librarian 1 - Collections - Regular Full-Time Burnaby , BC Description Burnaby Public Library is located on the ancestral and unceded homelands of the hən̓q̓əmin̓əm̓ and Sḵwx̱wú7mesh speaking peoples. We are grateful for the opportunity to work on this territory.Burnaby Public Library empowers the community to engage with and share stories, ideas and information. Our vision is a welcoming community where all people can explore, learn and connect.Burnaby is the third largest city in British Columbia, with excellent rapid transit links, significant parkland, and well-equipped recreational facilities. Our 250,000 residents speak 120 languages, and more than half of our culturally diverse population has a mother tongue other than English.BPL’s four libraries are important public spaces, meeting places and centres for discovery and dialogue, anchored by our broad and deep collections and our commitment to in-person service. BPL is changing to continue to meet the needs of our highly diverse community, with an increased emphasis on community-led approaches and connecting with people outside the library, a greater focus on digital literacy, and a commitment to upgrading and rethinking our public and staff spaces.__________________________________________________________________________________________Burnaby Public Library (BPL) invites applications from librarians interested in full-time work as of Tuesday January 9, 2024. Forward your resume and cover letter in confidence to careers@bpl.bc.ca and quote competition 2024-02. The closing date for this posting is Thursday January 18, 2024.Position Title: LIBRARIAN 1 – COLLECTIONSLocation: TECHNICAL SERVICES, BOB PRITTIE METROTOWN LIBRARYStatus: REGULAR FULL-TIMEPosition Summary:Burnaby Public Library invites applications for a full-time collections librarian with a passion for developing broad and deep library collections that respond to community needs. The successful candidate will join a collaborative team of four collections librarians with shared responsibility for the selection and maintenance of collections for adults, children and teens, in multiple formats and languages. This Librarian 1 position will focus on the evaluation, licensing and support of digital resources, and the selection and management of newspapers and magazines. The position also performs other collections work as needed, including selecting print and audio-visual materials for all audiences.This position spends approximately 20% of the time doing direct public service at a library branch (currently Metrotown and Tommy Douglas but subject to change) and reports to the Librarian 2, Collections.Duties: Oversees subscription resources in digital and print formats. Recommends, promotes and maintains digital resources for the system. Develops digital collections based on assigned budgets and makes recommendations regarding budget allocations as needed. Supports and acts as a resource for library staff using and promoting digital resources to library patrons. Compiles and evaluates usage statistics for digital resources, including e-books and audiobooks. Develops and manages collections in print and other formats as required. Liaises with library vendors on matters related to the work. Represents the library at vendor, library consortium, and other meetings and events.Provides welcoming, inclusive service to patrons of all ages in Burnaby’s culturally diverse community. Assumes responsibility for library premises and provides direct service to patrons in branch. Provides personal reference and information services that connect patrons with the resources and information that they need. Assist patrons with technology and with digital resources. Attends meetings, workshops, seminars, conferences and other organized activities related to the work. Spends approximately 20% of time doing direct public service and patron support.Qualifications: A master’s degree in librarianship. Knowledge and/or experience in the evaluation, licensing and support of digital resources, including e-books and downloadable audiobooks. Familiarity with acquisitions and collection management tools and approaches. High degree of comfort with technology and computer applications; strong analytical, problem solving and instructional skills. Ability to liaise with a variety of internal and external contacts. Ability to collaborate and communicate effectively with coworkers across branches and departments. Curiosity about the needs of library patrons and community members and a passion for building broad and deep library collections that respond to those needs. A commitment to the principles of intellectual freedom. Ability to select, purchase and allocate library materials in accordance with established budgets. A commitment to applying principles of equity, diversity, inclusion and anti-racism to the work. Knowledge of languages other than English is helpful to us. Reading knowledge of Chinese and/or Korean in particular is an asset in this position.Salary: $39.14 hourly, with 1.5% special benefit after 6 months per CUPE23 2022-2024 Collective AgreementHours: 75 hours biweekly. Weekend work will be required. Evening work may be required.The 9-day fortnight schedule (work 8.33 hours for 9 days and have the 10th day off) for this position is listed below.Week 1: Monday to Thursday 8:30-5:20, Friday/Saturday/Sunday OFFWeek 2: Monday to Thursday 8:30-5:20 Friday/Saturday OFF, Sunday 11:15-5:15**Shifts on Sundays will be 9:25-6:15 when we extend Sunday opening hours to 10am-6pm.Schedules are subject to change to meet operational needs. All staff may be asked to work in other locations at any time.We thank all applicants for their interest in Burnaby Public Library. We encourage you to apply even if you do not have all the qualifications we list here. Only those selected for an interview will be contacted.BPL believes that diversifying our staff will make our organization better and more reflective of the community we serve. We encourage people of all genders, ages, ethnicities, cultures, abilities, sexual orientations, and life experiences to apply. Compensation $39.14 hourly, with 1.5% special benefit after 6 months Closes: 18 January, 2024 Burnaby Public Library Burnaby , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
