Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Temporary Library Technician Castlegar , BC Description Castlegar &amp; District Public Library Job Posting: Temporary Library TechnicianThe Castlegar &amp; District Public Library has an opening for a Temporary Library Technician, from January 23, 2024, to December 23, 2024, with possibility of extension.Under the general supervision of the Library Director, the Library Technician is responsible for all aspects of circulation and ensures the smooth function of library computer systems.Specific Responsibilities:Maintain, update, and troubleshoot public access computers.Perform service desk duties, including but not limited to circulation, reference/readers advisory, supervising pages, and scanner/photocopier assistance.Assist patrons using public access computers, eBook and audiobook services, and library databases as needed.Prepare Interlibrary Loan and Interlibrary Connect items for mailing.Catalogue library media.Sort library donations for additions to library collection or book sale.Perform software installations and computer updates on staff computers as required.Maintain lendable technology and resolve problems as they arise.Manage and update the library website.Report monthly library databases statistics and compile new booklists.Contact and communicate with outside technical support as necessary.Maintain the volunteer list and schedule, and orientate new volunteers.Assist with other duties as required.Required knowledge, ability and skills:Skill and knowledge of library automated systems.Strong working knowledge of computer hardware and software systems.Ability to deal courteously, effectively and efficiently with the public and maintain effective working relationships with other employees.Ability to operate and troubleshoot common office equipment.Detail-oriented with good organizational and communication skills.Ability to undertake moderate physical activities that may include bending, reaching and lifting moderate weight.Desirable training and experience:Library Technician diploma OR equivalent library training and experience in a Library preferred.Hours, Salary &amp; Benefits:29.50/hour with benefits as per the CUPE Collective Agreement. Full-time (35 hours per week) Monday 10 am – 6 pm, Tuesday-Friday 9 am – 5 pm.Please submit resumes with cover letters to Alex Seaborn director@castlegarlibrary.com Closing Date: January 22, 2024 Compensation 29.50 Closes: 22 January, 2024 Castlegar &amp; District Public Library Castlegar , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
