Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Secondary Library Technician Mississauga , ON Description Extraordinary lives start with a great Catholic education.The Dufferin-Peel Catholic District School Board is a dynamic board committed to the delivery of quality educational programs and services. DPCDSB has over 73,000 students enrolled in 151 schools throughout Mississauga, Brampton, Caledon and Orangeville. We are one of the largest employers in the region with approximately 8,000 employees in an increasingly diverse community.We are currently accepting applications for the position of:Library Technician (Secondary Library Technician)Salary Range: $1,073.55 - $1,231.91 weeklyWork Schedule: 10 months/year, as requiredHours: 8:00 am – 4:00 pm Hours listed are current, but may be subject to changePOSITION SUMMARY:Under the direction of the Supervisor: Library Support Services, the Secondary Library Technician is responsible for providing administrative, technical, reference services to support the library function in the school. Maintaining confidentiality is a requirement of this position.BASIC QUALIFICATIONS:Diploma in Library and Information Technology from a recognized collegeMinimum 2 years in a relevant library setting in an educational or public service environment.Experience with emerging cloud, e‐learning, and collaboration technologies.Proficient in the use of Board sanctioned computer‐based technologies and electronic resources to create, manipulate, store and retrieve information, and communicate with othersExcellent communication and interpersonal skillsExcellent computer skills and familiarity Microsoft Office software applicationsMust have access to a reliable vehicle and hold a valid Ontario driver’s license to travel to multiple board sitesFamiliarity with an Integrated Library System, preferably SymphonyFamiliarity with online collaboration productivity tools.Previous experience conducting training/coaching sessions preferred.And· Evidence from previous work history of satisfactory attendance and punctualityFor more details regarding the job description please contact us contact us at (905) 890-0708 extension 24436 or visit www.dpcdsb.orgALL new employees will be required to submit a current original criminal background check (CBC) including a "Vulnerable Sector Screening" (VSS) issued within 6 months prior to commencing employment with the Board.We actively encourage applications from members of groups with historical and/or current barriers to equity, including, but not limited to: • First Nations, Métis and Inuit peoples, and all other Indigenous peoples; • members of groups that commonly experience discrimination due to race, ancestry, colour or place of origin; • persons with visible and/or invisible (physical and/or mental) disabilities.If you require a disability related accommodation in order to participate in the recruitment process, please contact us at (905) 890-0708 extension 24436 to provide your contact information. Support Services staff will contact you within 2 business days. The Dufferin-Peel Catholic District School Board is an equal opportunity employer. We will accommodate your needs under the Ontario Human Rights Code.We thank all applicants and advise that only those under consideration will be contacted. Compensation Salary Range: $1,073.55 - $1,231.91 weekly Closes: 2 February, 2024 Dufferin Peel Catholic District School Board Mississauga , ON Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
