eeking a team member who:is curious/inquisitivetakes responsibility for their workenjoys working with people of diverse backgrounds and perspectivescommunicates effectivelyis a critical thinkerhas a willingness to learnis familiar with library trends and technologyis able to adapt to changeis consistent and accurate in handling information, using established methods and procedurespractices sustained attention to detail The applicant should have experience with:Information organization and retrieval in a library environmentIntegrated Library Systems (ILS) – (Capilano University Library uses Sierra)Microsoft Office (Word, Excel, Outlook &amp; PowerPoint)Graphical design platforms such as Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Acrobat, Adobe Illustrator and Microsoft PublisherQualificationsLibrary Technician Diploma from a recognized post-secondary institution.One year of relevant library experience.For more informationFor more information, please see the complete job description here.BenefitsAt Capilano University, we understand that there is more to life than work. That is why we offer comprehensive benefits and support to help you and your family live a balanced life.Take a sneak peek to see what it is like to work at Capilano University.Posting Detail InformationDays and Hours of WorkOur standard work week is 35 hours per week.Work is conducted primarily on campus, However, CapU offers some flexibility in working conditions and there is an opportunity to request compressed work schedules for modified work weeks.Hours of work from Sept – April are as follows:Monday – Thursday, 2:30 p.m. – 10 p.m.Friday, 10:30 a.m. – 6:00 p.m.Hours of work from May – August are as follows:Monday -Friday, 9:30 a.m. – 5:00 p.m.Bridge Period (if applicable)Pay Group14Salary$49,000 annually based on 35 hours per week (with increments up to $55,000).UnionMoveUPJob Open Date01/05/2024Job Close Date01/19/2024Open Until FilledNoQuick Link for Postinghttps://jobs-capilanou.peopleadmin.com/postings/6453 Compensation $49,000 annually based on 35 hours per week (with increments up to $55,000) Closes: 19 January, 2024 Capilano University North Vancouver , BC Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
