Toggle navigation En français Browse Job Listings FAQ Contact Register Log in Log in Forgot password? Program Coordinator Vermilion , AB Description Vermilion Public Library serves a rural community in east central Alberta. We connect our community by providing and promoting library and information resources in a welcoming and accessible public space. Our major service goals for 2021-2025 include providing access to lifelong learning through new experiences and ideas, offering a hub for community building, and developing readers for life. We are seeking a part-time program coordinator (0.6 FTE) to help us meet our service goals by developing, coordinating, and evaluating our library programs and community outreach services. Essential Duties:1. Plan and deliver youth and adult programs to meet the library’s service goals through partnerships,training and recruiting facilitators, or delivering the program directly.2. Assist the library manager in building partnerships and community contacts to promote libraryservices and programs to the public. Identify and develop a list of key community contacts.3. Develop marketing strategies in partnership with Media personnel for all programs and events4. Brief staff on all ongoing programs and report regularly to the library manager on ongoing programs5. Serve as the lead on reporting, recording, and analysis of data in relation to the library’sprogramming goals and objectives. Prepare a variety of reports and surveys to evaluate success.Secondary Duties:1. Perform basic circulation desk procedures such as circulation, registration, and cash transactionsQualifications:Graduation from a Library Technician program or diploma/degree in a related field; OR a minimum of 2years of experience in public library service or event planning; OR any equivalent combination ofeducation and experience that demonstrates the ability to perform the essential duties.Knowledge, Skills and Abilities:- Considerable knowledge of rural communities, community networking and outreach techniques.- Plan, manage, and evaluate projects and programs from concept to completion, within budget and deadline; revise and adjust ongoing programs to meet library objectives; multitask and coordinate a variety of concurrent projects and activities.- Considerable knowledge of internet applications, social media, mobile devices, and office software.- Working knowledge of FOIP and the principles of intellectual freedom- Social media management, using office computer hardware and softwarePlease apply with a cover letter and resume to librarian@vplibrary.ca Accepting applications until the position is filled. Compensation This position is 21 hours per week and is eligible for a competitive health benefits package and pension plan with LAPP. The hourly salary grid range for this position is $21.32 to $24.94. Up to 30% remote work is available as minimum on site staffing req Closes: 15 February, 2024 Vermilion Public Library Vermilion , AB Policies and Terms of Use · jobboard@bcla.bc.ca / BCLA PO BOX 19008, Rocky Point PO, Port Moody, BC V3H 0J1 window.dataLayer = window.dataLayer || [];
